@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="dark-page-section py-4 py-lg-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="dark-page-shell">
            <div class="dark-page-hero mb-4">
                <span class="dark-page-badge">Privacy Policy</span>
                <h1 class="dark-page-title mt-3">Privacy and data protection</h1>
                <p class="dark-page-subtitle mb-0">
                    LifeAdmin is designed as a personal productivity application with focus on secure access,
                    basic data protection, and responsible handling of user-generated content.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="dark-page-card">
                <p class="dark-updated mb-4">Last updated: April 2026</p>

                <div class="dark-policy-section">
                    <h2 class="dark-section-title">1. Information we store</h2>
                    <p>
                        LifeAdmin stores basic account information such as username and email,
                        along with user-generated content including tasks, notes, categories, and documents.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="dark-policy-section">
                    <h2 class="dark-section-title">2. Purpose of the data</h2>
                    <p>
                        The stored data is used only for the normal functionality of the application,
                        allowing users to create, manage, update, and organize their personal content.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="dark-policy-section">
                    <h2 class="dark-section-title">3. Data protection</h2>
                    <p>
                        The application uses ASP.NET Core Identity for authentication and authorization.
                        Access to personal content is restricted according to the authenticated user
                        and the authorization rules implemented in the system.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="dark-policy-section">
                    <h2 class="dark-section-title">4. Third-party sharing</h2>
                    <p>
                        LifeAdmin does not share personal data with third parties.
                        The application is created for educational and portfolio purposes as part of the SoftUni training program.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="dark-policy-section mb-0">
                    <h2 class="dark-section-title">5. Contact and project scope</h2>
                    <p class="mb-0">
                        This project is intended as a learning and portfolio application.
                        The privacy page is included to demonstrate awareness of secure application structure,
                        responsible data handling, and clear communication with users.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>